@invobj
#cycle 1
(The double doors open. A platform rises
from a sub-basement until it is level with
the ground. Standing on it are a crop-
duster and Sartorio. The haggard sorcerer
wears a gray flight suit and a green iron
key around his neck.)
/i
Burns: The blowers are defused, and you
are NOT taking off in that thing. I can
guess what you've replaced the dust with.

(Sartorio shows no reaction.)
/i
Sartorio: Nyarlethole enjoys drama. The
Four Elements theme was his idea. Two
wings of the building were destroyed to
achieve the effect. The crop duster was my
plan. Practical. Simple. Effective.

Burns: You are a sick, sick man.
/i
Sartorio: And you are a dead, dead
woman.

(Sartorio begins a series of complicated
gestures.)
/i
(Burns shoots him.)

Burns: And you are a trite, trite villain.
/i
(She walks over to the plane and snaps
off the throttle.)

Burns: (walking away) Poor fellow.
Probably thought that there would have to
be some big battle or something. Never
thought that I would just shoot him. Oh,
well. Anticlimax happens.
/i
Sartorio: Perhaps you should improve your
technique.

(Burns turns around. Sartorio is standing,
unharmed. He tosses an empty vial of
healing potion over his shoulder, and
lobs a fireball at Burns. She dives behind
the control panel, and the fight begins.)
/i
(Instructions:

During this battle, Sartorio will try to
draw a bead on Burns and flame her. His
crosshairs appear behind Burns; if Burns
is not behind cover and the crosshairs
line up with her, Sartorio will shoot her.
To prevent this, Burns must duck behind
the control panel whenever Sartorio is
about to aim at her.

As an aid to the player, Burns will
immediately duck behind cover if she is
hit, preventing her from being shot again.
/i
At the same time, Burns must attempt to
shoot Sartorio. Her crosshairs are behind
Sartorio. Since he moves, Burns must
correct her aim constantly, lining up
her crosshairs with her target. She can
only aim when she is out of cover, and
can only shoot when her laser is at full
power (lower left bar). Shooting or
pulling the trigger when there isn't
enough power resets the power meter.

Oh, and remember: Sartorio can dodge your
shots occasionally. Don't be surprised if
a seemingly good shot misses.
/i
Controls:

Up and down arrows: Aim (line up
crosshair)

Right arrow: Shoot

Left arrow: Take cover
/i
